<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906297>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 2. — Five small intercentra (A-C, NMT RB464; D-F, NMT RB465; G-I, NMT RB466; J-L, NMT RB467; M-O, NMT RB468) of small cf. Stereospondyli from the Triassic (?Anisian) of Tanzania (Ruhuhu Basin) in anterior (A, D, G, J, M), lateral (B, E, H, K, N), and ventral (C, F, I, L, O) views. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4906297/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906301>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Ten atlantes (NHCC LB647, 679-687) of small adults of cf. Stereospondyli from the Triassic (?Anisian) of Zambia (Luangwa Basin) in dorsal (A) and anterior (B) views; B, NHCC LB647 is figured to show the two articular facets with the occipital condyles. Scale bar: 10 mm. Modified from Peecook et al. 2018." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4906301/files/figure.png" .

